{"id":"d=origam-topic-2313//p=4cebf7e1f2aa432e9426b6d18cd66533","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-2313"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["acfff702c336451aa0c5947ae24b6ca0"],"__file_part":["6c33c7e34de4430e9c63515dc6e533c0"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["2313"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/problem-reporting-configuration/2313"],"title":["Problem Reporting Configuration"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# Problem Reporting Configuration\n\nCategory: docs\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/problem-reporting-configuration/2313\n\n@system (2017-12-31 23:00:00Z):\n   Problem Reporting Configuration \n This page describes steps to configure problem reporting feature. \n Problem reporting configuration is stored in external file, which is linked from web.config. \n First there has to be config section added to the web.config file: \n  Config section in web.config  \n  \u003CconfigSections\u003E\n    \u003Csection name=\u0022problemReportingSettings\u0022 type=\u0022System.Configuration.NameValueFileSectionHandler, System, Version=1.0.3300.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b77a5c561934e089\u0022/\u003E\n\u003C/configSections\u003E\n\u003CproblemReportingSettings file=\u0022problemReporting.config\u0022/\u003E\n  \n Content of problem reporting configuration file is following: \n  problemReporting.config  \n  \u003CproblemReportingSettings\u003E\n  \u003Cadd key=\u0022fromMail\u0022 value=\u0022no-reply@asap.is\u0022/\u003E\n  \u003Cadd key=\u0022toMail\u0022 value=\u0022name@domain.cz\u0022/\u003E\n\u003C/problemReportingSettings\u003E\n  \n There are two keys specifying parameters for the e-mails sent via problem reporting feature.  toMail  contains address, to which problems reports are sent.  fromMail  key contains address, which will appear as a sender in the sent problem report. \n Finally, the smtp configuration has to be specified ( http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms164240(v=vs.110).aspx  and  http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms164242(v=vs.110).aspx ) \n    \u003Csystem.net\u003E\n    \u003CmailSettings\u003E\n      \u003Csmtp from=no-reply@service.com\u0022\u003E\n        \u003Cnetwork host=\u0022smtp.mailservice.com\u0022 port=\u002225\u0022 userName=\u0022my-mail-username\u0022 password=\u0022my-mail-password\u0022 /\u003E\n      \u003C/smtp\u003E\n    \u003C/mailSettings\u003E\n  \u003C/system.net\u003E\n  \n Make sure that the \u201CfromMail\u201D from \u003CproblemReportingSettings\u003E is authorized to send emails from the defined smtp server. Note, that \u003Csmtp\u003E \u201Cfrom\u201D email address is not used for problem reporting! \n When sending a mail via smtp fails, the mail is attempted to send by \u201Cmailto\u201D functionality via default e-mail client program, but in that case the mail is without details (no backtrace) and is sent to address \u003Csupport@asap.is.\u003E This mail address can\u2019t be changed by configuration. That is a fallback functionality.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:23:47"},"vector":[-0.011298892,-0.011100041,-0.04117631,0.030058526,-0.017966894,-0.021936407,0.019154623,-0.0027674406,0.009191019,0.021279277,0.028062463,0.030901609,0.005703266,0.00090340764,0.0020002313,0.019073019,-0.017560698,0.0036774778,0.0007258058,0.011645183,0.019557519,-0.008977646,0.06131329,-0.0208403,-0.012415942,0.01127996,-0.05497615,-0.0124702,0.034723405,0.0009822672,-0.012783504,-0.049115278,0.011340705,-0.03759614,-0.014123265,-0.029117275,-0.003584586,-0.03624453,-0.02428923,0.02363186,-0.03606932,-0.002393339,-0.013872577,-0.033108708,0.029183917,-0.0072424,-0.0034735338,-0.014998207,0.024236305,0.00551355,-0.0022197575,-0.028137263,0.022567376,-0.06847813,0.045519058,0.06647581,-0.0009812119,-0.012342538,-0.017638288,0.003281505,-0.027310332,0.00882312,-